name: Cao Cao, Lord of Wei
text: {T}: Target opponent discards two cards. Activate this ability only during your turn, before attackers are declared.

name: Captain Sisay
text: {T}: Search your library for a legendary card, reveal that card, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Her leadership forged the Weatherlight's finest crew.

name: Doran, the Siege Tower
text: Each creature assigns combat damage equal to its toughness rather than its power.
flavor: "Each year that passes rings you inwardly with memory and might. Wield your heart, and the world will tremble."

name: Kiki-Jiki, Mirror Breaker
text: Haste\n{T}: Put a token that's a copy of target nonlegendary creature you control onto the battlefield. That token has haste. Sacrifice it at the beginning of the next end step.

name: Kresh the Bloodbraided
text: Whenever another creature dies, you may put X +1/+1 counters on Kresh the Bloodbraided, where X is that creature's power.
flavor: Each of his twenty-two braids is bound with bone and leather from a foe.

name: Mikaeus, the Lunarch
text: Mikaeus, the Lunarch enters the battlefield with X +1/+1 counters on it.\n{T}: Put a +1/+1 counter on Mikaeus.\n{T}, Remove a +1/+1 counter from Mikaeus: Put a +1/+1 counter on each other creature you control.

name: Omnath, Locus of Mana
text: Green mana doesn't empty from your mana pool as steps and phases end.\nOmnath, Locus of Mana gets +1/+1 for each green mana in your mana pool.
flavor: It gathers against the coming storm.

name: Oona, Queen of the Fae
text: Flying\n{X}{U/B}: Choose a color. Target opponent exiles the top X cards of his or her library. For each card of the chosen color exiled this way, put a 1/1 blue and black Faerie Rogue creature token with flying onto the battlefield.

name: Progenitus
text: Protection from everything\nIf Progenitus would be put into a graveyard from anywhere, reveal Progenitus and shuffle it into its owner's library instead.
flavor: The Soul of the World has returned.

name: Rafiq of the Many
text: Exalted (Whenever a creature you control attacks alone, that creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.)\nWhenever a creature you control attacks alone, it gains double strike until end of turn.

name: Sharuum the Hegemon
text: Flying\nWhen Sharuum the Hegemon enters the battlefield, you may return target artifact card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: To gain audience with the hegemon, one must bring a riddle she has not heard.

name: Sun Quan, Lord of Wu
text: Creatures you control have horsemanship. (They can't be blocked except by creatures with horsemanship.)
flavor: "One score and four he reigned, the Southland king: / A dragon coiled, a tiger poised below the mighty Yangtze."

name: Teferi, Mage of Zhalfir
text: Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)\nCreature cards you own that aren't on the battlefield have flash.\nEach opponent can cast spells only any time he or she could cast a sorcery.
flavor: To save this plane, he must forsake all others.

name: Ulamog, the Infinite Gyre
text:
When you cast Ulamog, the Infinite Gyre, destroy target permanent.
Indestructible
Annihilator 4 (Whenever this creature attacks, defending player sacrifices four permanents.)
When Ulamog is put into a graveyard from anywhere, its owner shuffles his or her graveyard into his or her library.

name: Visara the Dreadful
text: Flying\n{T}: Destroy target creature. It can't be regenerated.
